<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-084-008 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 101 125</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  August 12 1991 v8 n32 p101(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;ne</JOURNAL><TITLE>SPC blames slump for worldwide cuts. (layoffs) (SoftwarePublishing Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brennan, Laura.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software Publishing Corp. (Personnel management).andO;Ticker:    SPCO.andO;Topic:     LayoffReorganizationWork Force Reduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>--------------------SPC Blames SlumpandM;For Worldwide CutsandM;Blaming declining sales and a recent restructuring, Software Publishing Corp.andO;(SPC) last week announced a 6 percent reduction in its worldwide work force.andM;The Mountain View, Calif., software maker laid off 45 workers, bringing itspayroll down to 735 employees, company officials said.andM;SPC recently paid $25.4 million for Precision Software Ltd., a Surrey,England, developer of a relational database for Windows.andP;  In June, thecompany consolidated its North American operations, creating some overlap instaff, according to SPC President Fred Gibbons.andM;The acquisition, consolidation and reorganization are intended to maintainSPC's profitability as it struggles with decreased demand for its existingapplications, Gibbons said.andP;  SPC suffered a particular decline in demand forHarvard Graphics in anticipation of the June release of Harvard Graphics 3.0.andM;Sales for SPC's third quarter, ended June 30, dropped to $32 million from $38million the year before.andP;  Profits dipped to $7 million, less than half the$16 million SPC earned in the same period in 1990.andM;-- Laura BrennanandM;</TEXT></DOC>